Privacy Policy
STORMX develops and provides mobile game services that entertain people around the world. This Privacy Policy (“Policy”) describes how and when STORMX (“We”, “Us”, or “Our”) collects, manages, uses, and shares your information when you (“You”, “Players” or “Users”) use our services. This Privacy Policy applies to STORMX' games, websites and related services, which we here collectively call the Service.
The scope of this Policy is limited to the information collected or received by STORMX through your use of the Service. STORMX is not responsible for the actions of third parties – people or companies – their use of information you provide to them, or any products or services they may offer. By using the Service, you are expressing your agreement to this Policy and the processing of your data in the manner provided in this Policy. If you do not agree to these terms, please do not use the Service.
Third-party Privacy Policy
Except as otherwise discussed in this Privacy Policy, this Privacy Policy only addresses the use and disclosure of information we collect from you. Other sites accessible through our site have their own privacy policies and data collection, use and disclosure practices. Please consult each site’s privacy policy. We are not responsible for the policies or practices of third parties.
Some parts of our Services are provided by a third-party Service Providers, who may collect and record information about your use of our Services. Additionally, other companies that place advertisements on our Websites, Games and/or Applications may collect information about you when you view or click on their advertising through the use of cookies. We cannot control the activities of such third parties and cannot guarantee that they will adhere to the privacy and security practices same or similar to ours.
Information Collection and Usage
Game Play Data
Whenever you play our games, we collect data about all of your interactions with the game and with other players. The Information we collect may include Player ID, your progress in the game, IP address, device ID and/or other information that, we believe, is necessary to improve user/your experience and maintain the quality of our Service.
User Device and Location
This information is needed to provide troubleshooting solutions and to understand the usage trends of our customers. The information we collect may include unique device ID, hardware type, MAC address, IMEI, OS, device name, email address, advertising ID, location, IP, and/or other location-based information.
The data listed above can be used to track the content you access in connection with the Service and your online behavior or to deliver, target and improve our advertising and the Service. For information on how to opt-out from personalized advertisements, see section “Opt-out of targeted advertising” below.
With your full consent, we may collect and process information on your precise location. We will use this information only to enhance the immediate game experience via functions like Nearby Friend finding, matching or similar.
Third-Party Login Services
When you log in to our games or websites using third-party login services (“Login Service”) such as Facebook Connect, Apple’s Game Center or Google+, the Login Services will provide you the option to share your personal information with us. Your personal information we receive via Login Services may include your name, email address, user ID, city, state or country you live, sex, birth date, profile picture. We may collect and record information through the Login Service in accordance with the policies and terms of that Login Service.
Information collected will be used to create your account, verify your identity when you log in, and allow you to play our games and use our Service. Services such as Facebook Connect give you the option to post information about your activities on our games. If you want us to delete the data we receive from Facebook, Game Center or Google+ about you, please contact us at dev@stormxgames.com.
Friend Contacts
STORMX may provide several options to invite your contacts from Social Network Services or Platforms (such as Facebook, VK.com, Twitter, QQ, etc.) so that those contacts can be located in our games.
Your contact information will be used only for the purpose of sending communications to the addressee. You or a third party may contact us at dev@stormxgames.com to request the removal of this information from our database.
Customer Support
We may need to collect your email address in order to respond when you contact our Customer Support Team. We may use the email address to contact you about your gaming experience with our games and notify you about company news and promotions. If you no longer wish to receive certain email notifications, you may opt-out any time by emailing us at dev@stormxgames.com.
When you contact our Customer Support Team, we may also collect your device information (such as your OS version and device model), location-based information, Player ID or device ID, and your service request information to provide proper solutions in troubleshooting situations.
Payment Information
We may collect certain payment information from you on behalf of our payment service providers when you purchase our product or services, but this information is only temporarily stored so that it is unreadable by us. We do not collect or store any payment information from you.
Forum and Private Conversations
We may collect any information you provide in the public forum and private conversations for the purpose of improving user experience. The scope of a Private Conversation is limited to the exchange of ideas or messages using our Services. Chatting with other players in our games or privately messaging other players on our forum are examples of Private Conversations. Please note that any information you provide on the forum and private conversations may be read, collected, and used by others who access them. To request removal of your personal information from our community forum, contact us at dev@stormxgames.com.
To improve user experience, we may collect your email address when you register on the forum. The email address you provide will be mainly used to notify you about major policy changes or news regarding the usage of the forum. We may use the email address to contact you about your gaming experience with our games and notify you about company news and promotions. If you no longer wish to receive certain email notifications, you may opt-out any time by emailing us at dev@stormxgames.com.
Websites and Social Media Features
When you visit our sites, we may collect your personal information for the purpose of improving user experience on the sites. Such information may include your device OS, location, browser type, language, referring web address, your usage of the site, gender, age, interests.
Our websites may include Social Media Features, such as the Facebook Like button and Widgets, such as Share button or interactive mini-programs that run on our site. These Features may collect your IP address, which page you are visiting on our site, and may set a cookie to enable the Feature to function properly. Social Media Features and Widgets are either hosted by a third party or hosted directly on our Site. Your interactions with these Features are governed by the Privacy Policies of the companies providing them.
Other Cases
We may acquire information from you through your access and participation in message boards/forums, participation in surveys or contest through our Service. Certain information / personal information will be requested when you participate in some of our services. Participation in these sweepstakes or contests is voluntary which means you have a choice whether or not to provide us with such information. The requested information may include contact information (name, address, etc.) and demographic information (zip code).
